+/* MP6 native port -- B2 (docs/B2_BONUS_SPRITE.md). game/sprman.c's
+ * mp6_animCache (its own M3 fix, docs/M3_HSF.md) is a persistent side
+ * table keyed by raw pointer value, with entries removed only via
+ * HuSprAnimKill (i.e. only for objects torn down one at a time, tracked by
+ * refcount). It has no way to notice a BULK, non-destructor reclaim of the
+ * memory it describes -- exactly what the two calls below are: real
+ * hardware's own "does this look like a real pointer or a small file
+ * offset" content check (the mechanism this cache replaced) was immune to
+ * this by construction (computed fresh from whatever bytes are AT an
+ * address, every call), but a persistent side-table keyed by address is
+ * not. Declared here (not in a shared header) to keep this a narrowly
+ * scoped, single-purpose hook. */
+extern void mp6_animCacheClear(void);
+
